data.title: Minnesota Timberwolves Color Codes Hex, RGB, and CMYK
data.meta_description: The Minnesota Timberwolves colors are Midnight Blue, Lake Blue, Moonlight Grey, Aurora Green and White. This page includes their Hex, RGB, HSB and CMYK color codes.
data.text:
The Minnesota Timberwolves colors are midnight blue, lake blue, moonlight grey, and aurora green. The Minnesota Timberwolves team colors in Hex, RGB, and CMYK can be found below. The Minnesota Timberwolves are a team from Minneapolis, Minnesota. The biggest rivals of the Minnesota Timberwolves are the Milwaukee Bucks.

Minnesota Timberwolves Logo Colors

The Minnesota Timberwolves logo colors are midnight blue, lake blue, moonlight grey, and aurora green. The midnight blue color code for the Minnesota Timberwolves logo is Pantone: PMS 289 C, Hex Color: #0C2340, RGB: (12, 35, 64), CMYK: (100, 76, 12, 70). The lake blue color code for the Minnesota Timberwolves logo is Pantone: PMS 647 C, Hex Color: #236192, RGB: (35, 97, 146), CMYK: (96, 54, 5, 27). The moonlight grey color code for the Minnesota Timberwolves logo is Pantone: PMS 422 C, Hex Color: #9EA2A2, RGB: (158, 162, 162), CMYK: (19, 12, 13, 34). The aurora green color code for the Minnesota Timberwolves logo is Pantone: PMS 368 C, Hex Color: #78BE20, RGB: (120, 190, 32), CMYK: (65, 0, 100, 0).

Minnesota Timberwolves Logo

The Minnesota Timberwolves logo has midnight blue, lake blue, moonlight grey, and aurora green colors with a howling wolf in front of a blue basketball and a star object on top of it. The Minnesota Timberwolves logo meaning symbolizes the fierceness of the team as one united group with the howling of the timber wolf while the North Star symbolizes Minnesota pride.
